  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Matinyani &amp; Makindu Drought Response</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Construct wells, boreholes, and pipelines. Promote teaching of hygiene by Community Health Workers, distribute chlorine tablets. Plant drought-resistant crops, provide food and Vitamin A supplements and de-worming to children,  introduce vegetable and fruit seedlings. Provide lab testing, curative services, immunizatons and maternal and child health care through medical camps. Distribute food to the severly malnourished.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Matinyani &amp;amp; Makindu drought response focuses on constructing boreholes for water collection, working on sanitization practices, and leading conservation projects</narrative>
  </description>
